RT @BizarreNewsA Mid-City man who apprehended a trespasser in his City Park area home said he "had no other choice but to tie him to a post until police got there."

Using half a ratchet strap, some electrical wire and other construction-related items, Eric Hernandez tied the intruder to a post at around noon Wednesday and waited 90 minutes for police to arrive, he says. In the meantime, he got a haircut.

https://www.nola.com/news/crime_police/article_b5b95414-b115-11ec-8592-b31bfc7db827.html
